\caption{The AGN inner disc inclination ($i_{\rm ref}$) derived from fitting the reflection spectrum plotted against the inclination of the host galaxy stellar disc ($i_{\rm opt}$). The red line indicates a 1:1 correlation and we find, from performing a Pearson product-moment correlation test against the entire sample and Monte-Carlo simulations, that the sample is significantly ($\gg$ 5-$\sigma$) uncorrelated. If we assume that the sample is {\bf not} homogeneous then we find  that by removal of the five highlighted sources (red points), we can reproduce (at 3$\sigma$) the remaining sample distribution from an underlying 1:1 correlation. }


